JOHANNESBURG - Idols SA came to an end for singer Botlhale and social media was abuzz with criticism. Some users have called for an audit of the voter results. It was a bittersweet finish as South Africa bid farewell to Botlhale, whose journey ended just a week away from the grand finale. READ: SA Idols Top 3 jet off to London Before exiting the Idols stage, Botlhale got to make memories as part of the Top 3 whirlwind international tour. He, Paxton and Mthokozisi enjoyed a four-day tour of London before coming back home to record their singles, which they debuted on the show. Some viewers felt that the duet he sang with Amanda Black caused him a spot in the grand finale. eNCA